# monitor memory
watch -n 5 free -m
# add -h for human readable
# free is for memory
# watch -n 5 is every 5sec

# You want to look at the free column of the -/+ buffers/cache: row. This shows how much memory is available to applications..
             total       used       free     shared    buffers     cached
Mem:          3699       2896        802          0        247       1120
-/+ buffers/cache:       1528       2170
Swap:         1905         62       1843

# I know that I'm using 1528 MB and have 2170 MB free